# InkForm Project Rules

## Project Overview
InkForm is a Unity 2D platformer where the player switches between solid and fluid forms, featuring wall/ceiling climbing, spring-damping slime deformation, and more.

## Design Documents Location
All system design documents are located in `Assets/Perfab/Script/Project_Prompt/`:
- Player_Controller_Design.md — Player controller
- Skill_System_Design.md — Skill system
- Level_Objects_Design.md — Level objects
- Moving_Platform_Component_Design.md — Moving platform component
- Game_Event_System_Design.md — Game event system
- Manager_Systems_Design.md — Manager systems
- Level_Section_System_Design.md — Level section system
- CHANGELOG.md — Changelog

## Script Directory Structure
- `Assets/Perfab/Script/player/` — Player-related (S_Player, S_SkillBase, S_SkillTree, S_Soild_sprint, S_fluid_climb)
- `Assets/Perfab/Script/Manager/` — Managers (S_GameEvent, S_GameManager, S_UIManager)
- `Assets/Perfab/Script/LevelCon/` — Level controllers (S_MovingPlatform, S_LevelSection, S_LevelSectionController, S_SectionGoal)
- `Assets/Perfab/Script/` — Common level objects (S_BreakableBlock, S_CameraMove, S_Checkpoint, S_MoveBlock, S_Pipline)
- `Assets/Perfab/Script/tools/` — Utility scripts (S_coleve, S_setTrigger)
- `Assets/Scripts/` — Legacy scripts (SimpleMovement, PlayerTransform, WallWalker2D)

## Context Management Rules
- At the start of each task, read `memory-bank/activeContext.md` to understand current state
- Do not read all Project_Prompt documents at once — only load the ones relevant to the current task
- After completing a module, update `memory-bank/progress.md` and `memory-bank/activeContext.md`
- Proactively compress when context exceeds 50%

## Code Standards
- C# naming: PascalCase for classes and methods, camelCase for private fields
- In MonoBehaviours, use `[Header("Group Name")]` to group Inspector fields
- Use `AudioSource.PlayOneShot()` for one-shot SFX, `AudioSource.Play()`/`Stop()` for looping audio
- Physics movement goes in `FixedUpdate()`, input detection goes in `Update()`
- Moving platforms use delta displacement transfer (not SetParent) — calculate `transform.position` delta per frame and apply to player's Rigidbody2D
- Before adding a new system, check if a corresponding design document exists in `Assets/Perfab/Script/Project_Prompt/`. If it does, follow it strictly

## Documentation Maintenance Rules
- **Do not frequently modify design documents in Project_Prompt/ or CHANGELOG.md**
- Design documents and CHANGELOG should only be updated before major version pushes (e.g., v0.5.0, v0.6.0...)
- Small changes during daily development do not require design document updates

## Language Rule
- **All Project_Prompt/ design documents and CHANGELOG.md MUST be written in English**
- **All memory-bank/ files MUST be written in English**
- This ensures consistency and accessibility across the team

## Unity Version
- Unity 6000.1.17f1 (Unity 6)
- Unity Input System (new)
- Rigidbody2D (2D Physics)
- URP 2D Renderer

## Error Handling Rules
- When a Unity runtime bug is found, log it to `memory-bank/error-log.md` (symptom, root cause, fix, lesson learned)
- When fixing a logic bug, scan Project_Prompt/ design documents for cross-reference to check if other systems have the same problem
- After cross-reference fixes, log everything to `error-log.md`
- See the "Error Handling Rules" section in `.cline/skills/unity-dev/SKILL.md` for detailed workflow